  <text>
    <body>
      <ab type="lido:objectWorkType">Leaflet</ab>
      <ab subtype="creation" type="lido:event">
        <date>1955 after</date>
      </ab>
      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">The leaflet features a partly framed photograph with armed soldiers in uniform crossing a river on horseback. A mountainous landscape constitutes the backdrop. Written on the bottom of the frame is the Serbo-Croatian original film title, ‘Ešalon Dr. M.’ (Dr. M.’s echelon).</ab>
      <ab subtype="comment" type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">The film was directed by Živorad Žika Mitrović, a Serb, who developed a specific genre known as the ‘Kosovo western’ or ‘partisan western’. The genre has the form of a western but features content typical for partisan films. The film was released in 1955.</ab>
